SHORT TERM:

*	Add full checks for SRV, PTR, RP, and NAPTR to 'mydnscheck'. [Done: added strict validators for SRV owner/data, PTR targets, RP mailboxes, and full NAPTR field parsing in mydnscheck – Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>, 19-Nov-2025]

*  	Reply cache should obey shortest TTL in the cached RRSET. [Done via updated insert logic – Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>, 19-Nov-2025]



LONG TERM:

*	Move SRV/RP/NAPTR extra data OUT of the mydns_rr structure -- leave the
	data in the "data" column and let it be parsed as needed.  The parsed
	data really gobbles up space in the MYDNS_RR structure. [Done: canonicalise the data column and parse on demand – Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>, 19-Nov-2025]

*	Full IPv6 support (added to server, need support in utils). [Done: importer now uses IPv4/IPv6 sockets - Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>, 18-Nov-2025]

*	Update manual:
	- How delegation works.

*	LOC (RFC 1876) support. [Done: MyDNS now parses textual LOC data and emits RFC 1876 wire format. Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>, 19-Nov-2025]

*	Make sure we're NEVER using inet_ntoa, inet_addr, etc.  [Audit complete; only inet_ntop/inet_pton remain. Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>, 18-Nov-2025]

*	Fix in_cidr to work with IPv6 addresses. [Done via in_cidr_match(), legacy wrapper retained. Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>, 18-Nov-2025]

*	Test AXFR from an IPv6 master via `mydns-import'. [Done against a loopback MyDNS instance listening on [::1]+5400. Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>, 18-Nov-2025]

*	Investigate linker problem with `-ffast-math' on FreeBSD/alpha:

		/usr/lib/crtfastmath.o: In function `set_fast_math':
		/usr/lib/crtfastmath.o(.text+0x1c): undefined reference to
			`__ieee_set_fp_control'

*	No calls to gethostbyname() anywhere -- add `--enable-static-build'
	back to the `./configure' line in pkg/mydns-mysql.spec.in. [Both RPMs now pass --enable-static-build. Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>, 18-Nov-2025]


